{"questionId":"27496","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The overall equation for the production of hydrogen cyanide, HCN, is shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">CH<sub>4</sub> (g) + NH<sub>3</sub> (g) +<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>O<sub>2</sub> (g) → HCN (g) + 3H<sub>2</sub>O (g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the pH of a 1.00 × 10<sup>−2</sup> mol dm<sup>−3</sup> aqueous solution of ammonia.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">p<em>K</em><sub>b</sub> = 4.75 at 298 K.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Kb</em> = 10<sup>-4.75</sup> /1.78 x 10<sup>-5</sup><br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br><em>Kb</em> =&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mfrac><msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msup><mi>OH</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced></mfrac></math> ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[OH<sup>–</sup>] = «&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math> =» 4.22 × 10<sup>–4</sup> «(mol dm<sup>–3</sup>)» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>pOH« = –log<sub>10</sub> (4.22 × 10<sup>–4</sup>)» = 3.37<br><em><strong>AND</strong></em><br>pH = «14 – 3.37» = 10.6<br><em><strong><br>OR</strong></em><br><br>[H<sup>+</sup>]« =<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>14</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>» = 2.37 × 10<sup>–11</sup><br><em><strong>AND</strong></em><br>pH« = –log<sub>10</sub> 2.37 × 10<sup>–11</sup>» = 10.6 ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[3]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27496","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ2.7a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the pH of a 1.00 × 10−2 mol dm−3 aqueous solution of ammonia. pKb = 4.75 at 298 K.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 18: Acids and bases","18.2 Calculations involving acids and bases","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 18: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}